ion":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31064","headword_ar":"عَوْلٌ","root":"Ewl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawiylN","text_ar":"عَوِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eawola","text_ar":"عَوْلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a word like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayoba","text_ar":"وَيْبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eawolaka","text_ar":"عَوْلَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eawola zayodK","text_ar":"عَوْلَ زَيْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. May God decree"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy woe"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the woe of Zeyd,"},{"kind":"text","text":"virtually meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"woe to thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"woe to Zeyd"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, O, K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawolN lizayodK","text_ar":"عَوْلٌ لِزَيْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Woe to Zeyd"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, O:) or, accord. to Sb and others,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eawola","text_ar":"عَوْلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used only as a sequent to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayola","text_ar":"وَيْلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; they said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayolahu waEawolahu","text_ar":"وَيْلَهُ وَعَوْلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; in which, Az says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wyl","text_ar":"ويل"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ewl","text_ar":"عول"},{"kind":"text","text":"both signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weeping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lamentation with tears;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and Aboo- Tálib says that they are put in the accus. case as expressive of an imprecation and of blame, like as is done in the sayings"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayolFA lahu","text_ar":"وَيْلًا لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turaAbFA lahu","text_ar":"تُرَابًا لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"event, that renders one anxious:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA:) app. an inf. n. used thus as a subst. (TA.)       -A3-  And One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose aid is asked"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in affairs of difficulty"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"importance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaw~alN","text_ar":"مُعَوَّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A4-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"food of a family"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"household."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n31065","headword_ar":"عَوَلٌ","root":"Ewl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n31066","headword_ar":"عِوَلٌ","root":"Ewl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is [said to be] a subst. signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Reliance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confidence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * K, TA:) and [it is said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa EiwaliY","text_ar":"هُوَ عِوَلِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is my stay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"support:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the word, however, occurs in this form, twice, in a verse of Taäbata-sharrà, accord. to the relation thereof by Aboo-'Ikrimeh; but accord. to others it is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawalN","text_ar":"عَوَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E","text_ar":"ع"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":", and is said to be an inf. n.; whereas the former is said to be pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawolapN","text_ar":"عَوْلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [and the two words signify, respectively,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a weeping"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weepings;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for] by his saying"},{"kind":"quote","text":"l`kin~amaA EiawaliY A_ino EaiwalK"},{"kind":"text","text":"the poet means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If I wept"},{"kind":"text","text":"for any one,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I would weep"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiwalN","text_ar":"عِوَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also a subst. signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An asking for aid."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}